    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - Meritor Medium Duty Front Drive Steer Axle - Lubrication, Inspection and
        Maintenance - Cross Tube End Assembly
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="lubricate" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Cross Tube End Assembly</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check the cross tube for looseness of more than 0.060-inch (1.52 mm) (Figure 68). If loose,
                service as necessary.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0201268" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg02/G0201268.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 68. Check Cross Tube for Looseness</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. KNUCKLE BUSHING GREASE (ZERK) FITTING</callout1>
                <callout1>2. DRIVE FLANGE GREASE (ZERK) FITTING</callout1>
                <callout1>3. CROSS TUBE GREASE (ZERK) FITTING</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply the specified grease at the grease (zerk) fitting on the cross tube. Apply grease
                until new grease purges from all the seals.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If new grease does not purge at the seals, move the cross tube while applying grease at the
                fittings until new grease purges from all the seals. If new grease still does not purge, disassemble the
                cross tube. Inspect the grease and the components. Service as necessary.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
